-- UK's Wealth Management Association says CEO to step down
-- 
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 08:21AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 9 (Reuters) - UK trade body the Wealth Management Association (WMA) said on Wednesday that its chief executive, Tim May, would step down from his role later in the year to be replaced by Liz Field.

May, who has been CEO for four years, would begin handing over his duties to Field on Sept. 1 and leave after the group's annual conference on Oct. 6, the WMA said in a statement. Field was previously CEO of the Financial and Legal Skills Partnership.